JPA (Java Persistence API)

-> Eases the task of writing queries
-> Creates entities that are Java Objects and maps them back to a row in DB.
-> Hibernate is the ORM framework that created JPA standards.
-> JPA is an interface that defines set of annotations for creating the ORM.
    -> Hibernate is an implementation of JPA.
    -> Hibernate is most popular implementation of JPA, lightweight and easy to integrate.


Usage
-> Add the dependency to POM, reload the project, we should have the libraries to import
    -> Hibernate implementation is automatically configured (jar seen in maven dependencies folder)


